id: pm-z32q
title: "GH-498: pm comments rejects --body — accept it as an alias for --add and hint on unknown options"
description: "Upstream GH-498 (filed 2026-07-10). Agents trained on gh/glab reach for 'pm comments <id> --body ...' and hit 'Unknown option --body', costing a failed call plus a --help round-trip per fresh session on one of the highest-frequency write paths."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 3
tags[4]: agent-ux,cli,gh-issue,token-efficiency
created_at: "2026-07-10T16:20:02.384Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-10T16:22:00.814Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 45
acceptance_criteria: "pm comments <id> --body <text> behaves exactly like --add <text> (hidden alias, help stays lean); unknown-option errors on comments suggest the nearest valid flag (e.g. --body -> --add); contract/completion/docs sites updated per the new-flag wiring checklist; regression test covers alias and suggestion; GH-498 closed with a comment linking the fix"
risk: low
confidence: high
dependencies[2]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
