  pm-gdi7,related,"2026-07-10T16:22:00.795Z",null,null
body: "## Problem\n`pm comments <id> --body \"...\"` fails with `Unknown option --body`. gh/glab muscle memory makes --body the reflexive flag for comment text; every fresh agent session pays ~2 wasted tool calls + a few hundred tokens rediscovering --add. Observed in a real session 2026-07-10 (vanilla @unbrained/pm-cli 2026.7.10).\n\n## Proposed fix\n1. Accept `--body <text>` as a hidden alias for `--add <text>` on `pm comments` (and mirror for `--edit` replacement text if cheap).\n2. Extend the unknown-option error path to suggest the nearest valid flag — the unknown-COMMAND suggester exists; unknown-OPTION suggestions are the gap (ranking defect on the command side is pm-g543 / GH-490, related edge).\n\n## Scope guard\nAlias only — no behavior change to --add; help output must not grow (hidden alias) per token-efficiency goals.\n\n## Source\nhttps://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/498"
